The paper deals with optimization of coded caching, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the handling of non-uniform file length, popularity, and user cache size, which involves considerations of data structures (cs.DS) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also presents an optimization framework, which could be considered a machine learning approach (cs.LG) and discusses the interactions and influence of different heterogeneities, which could be considered a systems and information science approach (cs.SI).
